  "slug": "binding-the-pair",
  "title": "If the hybrid canary's weakness is that the distinctive tail detaches from the conventional hook as definitions mutate, could the hook and tail be structurally bound (the second sentence grammatically dependent on the first, so rephrasing the hook forces rephrasing the tail) — or does grammatical dependence push the pair back toward the merger line (the two sentences become one inseparable expression that merges with the idea)?",
  "url": "https://cambridgetcg.github.io/castle-gate/rooms/binding-the-pair",
  "summary": "Bind the lure to the hook and the fish cannot take one without the other — but a lure so bound is one piece, and one piece is harder to carve as yours.",
